RESEARCH Presentation

Research and Industrial Conclave is organizing Research Paper/Poster presentation competitions to showcase your work. Participants are requested to upload their detailed two page extended abstracts in the format displayed on the website. After screening, participants will be notified whether the abstract is selected for paper or poster presentation. Winners will be rewarded with exciting prizes. Following are the Departments/Centres/Schools under which participants can submit their abstract: 

Departments : Biosciences & Bioengineering, Chemical Engineering, Chemistry, Civil Engineering, Computer Science and Engineering, Design, Electronics & Electrical Engineering, Humanities and Social Sciences, Mathematics, Mechanical Engineering, Physics
Centres : Centre for Disaster Management and Research, Centre for the Environment, Centre for Indian Knowledge System, Center for Intelligent Cyber-Physical Systems, Centre for Linguistic Science and Technology, Centre for Nanotechnology, Centre for Sustainable Polymers,Centre for Drone Technology, Centre for Sustainable Water Research
Schools : School of Agro and Rural Technology, School of Business, Mehta Family School of Data Science and Artificial Intelligence, School of Energy Sciences and Engineering, School of Health Science & Technology 

 

We invite original and unpublished research papers from academia, industry, and research organizations on the following (but not limited to) Themes: 

Theme 1: Current Progress in Engineering Sciences (Chemical Engg., Civil Engg., Computer Science, Electrical & Electronics Engg., Mechanical Engg.)

Theme 2: Current Progress in Biochemical, Biomedical, and Physical Sciences  (Biosciences, Health-Sciences, Chemistry, Physics)

Theme 3: Current Progress in Interdisciplinary Research (Artificial Intelligence, Energy, Humanities & Social Sciences, Mathematics, Nanotechnology)

 

Instructions for Research Paper Presenters

  • The authors of each oral presentation have 10 minutes for presentation and 3 minutes for discussion.

  • The speakers should arrive at the venue for their oral presentation session at least 1 hour before the start of the session.

  • A system (windows) and LCD projector will be available to use for oral presentations.

  • All speakers should adhere strictly to the time allotted to their presentation.

  • Organisers will be around for any help.

Instructions for Poster Presenters

  • The authors should prepare a poster of size: 4 (height) X 3 (width) feet and carry this to the poster display area.

  • Organisers will be around to help with the poster display.

  • Speakers should adhere strictly to the time allotted to their presentation.

  • Please use the template provided in this website for making the poster.

Template

Abstract Submission Guidelines
A two-page  detailed extended abstract (inclusive of references, tables and figures) should be prepared in the following format:

  • Paper size: A4 (210 mm x 297 mm)

  • Line spacing: single

  • Font: Times New Roman, size 11

  • Page margins: 15 mm on left and right

  • Presenter author should be underlined and corresponding author should have asterisk (*)

  • Abstracts should be no more than2 pages, clearly outlining the research topic, methodology, key findings, and significance.
  • Full papers should follow the prescribed format (details will be provided upon acceptance of the abstract).

Abstract should be submitted in .doc/.docx format. Here is the Link for the template

Three Minutes Thesis Presentation

Ready to present your PhD work in an innovative way? Research and Industrial Conclave is organizing a competition to reward your presentation skills and your work. The rules pertaining to this competition are:

  • A single static PowerPoint slide is permitted (no slide transitions, animations or 'movement' of any description, the slide is to be presented from the beginning of the oration).

  • No additional electronic media (e.g. sound and video files) are permitted.

  • No additional props (e.g. costumes, musical instruments, laboratory equipment) are permitted.

  • Presentations are limited to 3 minutes maximum and competitors exceeding 3 minutes will be given negative marking (for each 10 seconds extra consumed, 1 mark will be deducted from the total score obtained by a participant).

  • Presentations are to be spoken word (e.g. no poems, raps or songs).

  • Presentations are to be commenced from the stage/virtual room.

  • Presentations are considered to have commenced when a presenter starts their presentation through movement or speech.

  • The decision of the adjudicating panel is final.

Participants are requestsed to upload their abstracts in the format displayed on this website. Winners will be awarded with exciting prizes.Here is the Link for Demo
